Alecia Beth Moore (born September 8, 1979), better known by her stage name Pink (often stylized as P!nk), is an American singer-songwriter, musician and actress. After her three-year career with the contemporary R&B girl group Choice, in 2000 she released her first single "There You Go," from her debut album Can't Take Me Home. The song garnered commercial success, peaking at #7 on the Billboard Hot 100. In 2001, she released her second, more pop rock-oriented, studio album, Missundaztood. The album went on to become a critical and commercial success. The album produced four singles, "Get the Party Started," "Don't Let Me Get Me," "Just Like a Pill" and "Family Portrait," each entering the Top 20, with "Get the Party Started" being her highest charting solo single (tied with "Most Girls":wink: until "So What" in 2008, peaking at #1 on the Billboard Hot 100.





Album Release Date: September 18, 2012

The Truth About Love is the sixth studio album by American recording artist Pink scheduled for release from September 18, 2012. The album will be Pink's first record under RCA Records after Sony Music reorganised its label operations closing down Pink's previous labels Jive Records and LaFace Records. The Truth About Love's first single "Blow Me (One Last Kiss)" was released on July 2012, so far peaking at number zhieesx on the US Billboard Hot 100, as well as charting inside the top ten in other several countries.
